The paper introduces and studies mechanisms, which are typically studied in game theory (cs.GT) and algorithmic mechanism design (cs.DS). The paper also discusses applications of these mechanisms in auction design (cs.EC) and scheduling (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of algorithms and optimization techniques, which fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
